Linear Modeling example using ’00’s market data

Stefan Skinner

2022-11-23

Brief Linear Model Project using market data from ’02 - ’05

This project uses a linear model to find connections between variables. In this case: Crude Oil, Silver, DJIA, Shenzhen, E-Mini S&P 500, & TSE.

All NA’s and null’s are left for imputation by MICE, after the removal of outliers to the median.

Statistically significant connections were found between E-Mini, DJIA, Shenzhen, and TSE; these connections are shown in ggplot2 graphs with geom_line.
